article.headline: Oral Roberts 78, Utah 70
article.story: SALT LAKE CITY -- Warren Niles came off the bench to score 20 points and Damen Bell-Holter added a career-high 18 as Oral Roberts beat Utah 78-70 on Saturday night. Dominique Morrison had 17 points and a career-high seven assists for the Golden Eagles (2-3), who led by 16 late in the first half but had to hold on for the win. Will Clyburn led the Utes (3-2) with 21 points and 10 rebounds. Josh Watkins added 18 points. Oral Roberts shot 52 percent from the field. Niles matched his career-best with five 3-pointers. Bell-Holter hit three 3-pointers, one more than his career total entering the game. Led by Niles, the Golden Eagles bench outscored the Utah reserves 28-12.
